    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Individuals who specialize in daguerreotypes, which are created by using an early photographic process (invented by L.J.M. Daguerre) that produces a direct positive image on a silver-coated copper plate.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
